Minisodes (2015–16)
|title=20|director=15|writer=15|airdate=10|episodes=
|ShortSummary    = Tom starts copying Hank's actions and words. After trying to get Tom to stop, Hank does a long crazy sequence of actions, but Tom claims that he missed it and makes Hank do it again, just so that Hank entertains him.
|LineColor       = #FFD700
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom finds the rest of the gang stuck in their chairs staring at their devices. Tom believes his hypnotising app works, but then his friends snap out of it and tell him that the app is boring and lame.
|LineColor       = #FFD700
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben does stand-up comedy involving science, but no one laughs. When he tries to explain his joke and starts tripping over cables and knocking over things, the audience laughs, much to Ben's chagrin.
|LineColor       = #FFD700
}}
|ShortSummary    = Hank makes Ginger vacuum the floor so he can eat Ginger's sandwich, but when Ginger catches Hank eating his sandwich, he vacuums the sandwich and Hank inside, puts the sandwich in the trash, and leaves.
|LineColor       = #FFD700
}}
|ShortSummary    = Hank wakes Tom from a dream, but Tom does not want to go to work, so Ben uses his robot to drag a cranky Tom out of bed.
|LineColor       = #FFD700
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom brings Ben a list of apps they could make, but Ben shows that all of them have already been created, and applies some of them on Tom.
|LineColor       = #FFD700
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom raps about Hank's custom bicycle, though Hank and Angela have no idea about what Tom is doing, with Angela quipping that even Tom does not know what he is doing.
|LineColor       = #FFD700
}}
|ShortSummary    = Angela is annoyed that the guys have forgotten her birthday and are making her do errands. In a fit of rage, she destroys the box she was supposed to carry to the garage, only to discover that her friends had planned a surprise birthday party and that she destroyed her own birthday cake.
|LineColor       = #FFD700
}}}}
Season 1 (2015–16)
in Season|title=20|director=15|writer=15|airdate=10|episodes=
|ShortSummary    = Tom and Ben plan to enter their anti-theft app in a prestigious app design contest, but Tom loses his voice when he accidentally electrocutes himself with the app. Dr. Internet Doctor recommends Tom not use his voice for a week. Ben tries to present their app by himself at the contest, however, Tom decides his friendship with Ben is more important and joins Ben on stage. The CEO accidentally electrocutes himself with the app when trying to use it, and a surprised Tom and Ben escape.
|LineColor = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = After Tom releases the Talking Ben app prematurely, customers are angry because Ben cannot fix bugs and handle customer service. Ben creates Gilbert, an answering machine robot. However, Ben programs Gilbert to not let anyone end the call until they become his friends. When Tom and Ben try to go to an amusement park with Angela, Gilbert wants to go too, and traps and electrocutes them in the garage until they are friends. An angry Angela yells at Tom and Ben for trying to become friends with Gilbert, but she gets trapped with Tom and Ben, and uses Gilbert's own logic to shut him down. However, after they do that, Ginger finds Gilbert and switches him on again.
|LineColor = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom and Ben meet another app developing duo, but that pair is fighting. Tom and Ben invent an app called the Future Tron 6000, allowing them to see their own futures.
|LineColor    = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = While Tom, Ben and Hank are filming a commercial for their Sing Like a Pro app, the gardener interrupts by running a leaf blower and then a jackhammer. After seeing Ginger shout to the gardener to stop making noise, the two invent a megaphone called the "Assertive App" which can command anyone who listens to it to do what the person says. However, Ginger gets a hold of the invention and misuses it to make Tom and Ben give him candy. Angela seems to be immune to commands made through the app, and also capable of interfering with the app, and stops Ginger from causing more trouble, destroying the megaphone in the process.
|LineColor     = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom and Ben plan to face Ginger and the gardener in a horseshoes event. However, Ben receives an invitation from a university, and decides to attend that instead of the finals. There, he discovers he is not going to be a colleague but a test subject who will be exposed to high doses of EMF. When he returns, he discovers he has become a magnet, and ends up getting hit with a horseshoe (which he attracted), knocking himself unconscious, and eliminating him and Tom from the finals.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Angela invites Tom to the "Scarf Spectacular Runway Neck-tacular" event where she is to be honoured as the Newcomer of the Year. She tells Tom not to embarrass her; however, when Tom starts promoting the idea of a scarf with unlimited design possibilities, he attracts the attention of a fashion company executive named Autumn Summers, who revokes Angela's award and gives it to Tom. Tom apologises to Angela and tries to include her work into the presentation of the app. When Autumn states that scarves are not for everyone, Angela gets offended and withdraws the idea. Tom and his friends make a website and app for Angela and her scarves that garners a lot of orders, only to realise that they forgot to put a price on the scarves and will not get paid for the scarves.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben records a how-to video for a Flappy Bird-style video game called "Flappy Talking Tom", where he plans to give Hank tips while the latter plays it. However, Hank turns out to be quite capable at the game, even beating Ben's high score. Hank challenges Ben to a match called the "Barrage in the Garage". Ben becomes stressed, while Hank is relaxed. Ben eventually collapses but wins the challenge. Ginger later beats Ben's score.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Angela has a concert at the park, but the visitors do not care for her singing. When Ginger posts photos of Angela getting upset and flipping a table, she starts becoming popular on a gossip channel's "Hot New Celebrity List". Angela hires Ginger as her new image consultant. Ginger then sets up a fake date between Tom and Angela to film them dramatically breaking up. When that video helps her, Angela has second thoughts about whether her celebrity image is more important than her singing career, and chooses her career.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom and the gang go on an annual camping trip in the desert. Ben secretly brings his computer along and uses it to flirt with the Moon. Tom is unhappy because Ben is away from their activities.
* Guest: Dannah Phirman as Ben's Mom, Moon
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = After the camping trip from the previous episode, Ben visits the Moon, his love interest. Back on Earth, work is difficult without Ben, and Tom misses Ben.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Hank has no money to buy a hamburger, so Tom suggests that he use a crowdfunding website called Cashkicker.  Hank asks for money to buy a hamburger, and promises to personally eat a hamburger with every funder. Hank's campaign raises one million dollars, while Ben's campaign for funding to make handheld holograms accessible to the public fails due to Ben's rudeness in his video. Hank spends all his money on hamburgers, but runs into trouble when he has to fulfill his promise. After he starts hallucinating and becomes paranoid, Tom gets an idea and tells Ben  to create hamburger holograms for Hank to pretend to eat in a personalised video for each of his funders.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom and the gang have a Scare-a-thon TV Marathon, but Ginger gets angry at the gang when they refuse to go trick-or-treating with him as they are adults. During the event, Ben uses his Total TV Immersion app to make it seem like they are in the show. When Ginger returns and starts capturing the gang by zapping them into his phone, Tom and his friends are forced to do what Ginger says.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = After Ben's stand-up act fails, Ben, believing that his jokes are funny, conducts research on how to make his act funnier. Ben concludes that being big will make him funnier, and uses his new invention, the Gain-a-Tron to make himself morbidly obese. His new act is very successful, but Tom and the gang are aware that the audience is just laughing at him because of his size and not his jokes. At Ginger's suggestion, Ben reads from a school yearbook in front of the crowd and realises that everyone is laughing at his size. Ginger arrives, morbidly obese because he had used the invention, and takes away Ben's popularity. Later, Ben decides to reverse his obesity, only to learn that Ginger had destroyed the invention while using it, and has Hank jump on him repeatedly instead.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ginger gets angry at Hank because he will not allow Ginger to watch the show he wants to watch. Ginger tricks Hank into thinking that Hank is an imaginary friend, and Hank believes it when the rest of the gang also ignores him. However, the prank later backfires when Ginger slips from the roof, and Hank does not save him because he thinks he is imaginary.
* ''Angela's Songs: "Imaginary Friend"
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = While working on an invention, Ben tries to keep his work area clean, quarantining Hank to the bathroom because of a cold, and using one of his inventions to find germs. When he misses one of the germs, he decides to enlarge it. The gang finds the germ, named Jeremy, to be cute. Jeremy tells Ben that he intends to make everyone sick, while pretending to be very sociable around the rest of the gang. Ben tries to convince his friends that Jeremy is evil. Ben resorts to flushing Jeremy down the toilet, only for everyone else to start showing symptoms.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Every year for his birthday, Hank asks the gang to help him make a fan-fiction episode of Bongo and McGillicuddy'', and this year they finally agree. Hank makes Tom and Ginger compete by auditioning for the lead role. He selects Tom, and makes Ginger his assistant. During filming, Hank becomes very irritated and rude in directing the work. He eventually realises how mean he was, and apologises.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = The gang waits for two days and three nights in line to get a Glove Phone, only to be turned away as the store is out of stock. After they learn that Ginger got one and will not share it, Tom tries to sneak into Ginger's house to take it, and realises that Ginger had set a trap for him. Ginger sarcastically claps for Tom while wearing the Glove Phone, only to end up damaging it beyond repair.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Three years before the series' events, Ben became so obsessed with ping pong that he would not go to work until someone defeated him in a match. Tom and his friends solicited the help of their landlord, who happened to be a former ping pong champion, and he defeated Ben.
* ''Angela's Songs'': "Ben the Ping Pong Wizard"
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = While trying to watch shows on his tablet, Hank accidentally clicks on a pop-up ad for Dr. Internet Doctor's Online Medical School, and ends up enrolling. He diagnoses Tom and the gang, and thinks Ben has a serious condition. Ben convinces himself of the same and is prepared to undergo an operation by Hank, even though Tom and Angela are against it.
|LineColor       = FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = When Angela is heckled during a Christmas performance, Ben blames Tom because he is the only one among them to have heckled at a Christmas performance. Angela also believes that Tom is the culprit, so Tom and Hank pretend to be British detectives to clear Tom's name. They discover that the culprit is Santa Claus, who heckled Angela because her song insulted reindeer.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ginger and Hank are having fun role-playing as kings of a cardboard fort, while Tom, Ben and Angela mind their own business. When Ginger and Hank take over the kitchen and insult Ben who wants to go to the kitchen, Ben, Tom, and Angela role-play as enemies and attack the fort to get revenge. Ginger and Hank to pretend to have jet packs, while Tom, Ben and Angela take over the fort and start role-playing themselves.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom has created an app that can guess a user's favourite smoothie, but it turns out to be very inaccurate. When he and his friends get a visit from the CEO, whose helicopter has crash-landed nearby, Tom tells his friends not to pitch their ideas to him or try to take advantage of him, but later promotes his app. Tom misinterprets the CEO's receptionist's hold music as supporting doing the wrong thing, and considers the CEO an enemy. The CEO forgives him after learning about why Tom did the wrong thing. The CEO is given Hank's defective snowmobile to return to the office, but crashes because of the defect.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = The landlord tells Tom and his friends that they have to leave the garage for a week as there is a volcano underneath that is erupting, so Angela offers to house them. Tom gets  nervous about impressing Angela and acts weirdly. Ben tries to calm Tom down, and accidentally breaks Angela's belongings. In anger, Angela calls a house meeting and says that Tom must find elsewhere to live, and Tom leaves, dejected. That night, Angela and Ginger find Tom in the garage, surrounded by a lake of lava, and persuade him to return.
|LineColor = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = The gang gets ready for a video game match, only for it to be cancelled due to a power outage. They panic as their phones are also dead. Tom notes that they have become too reliant on technology, and while checking the mailbox, he finds a letter containing one ticket to the Floppy Disk Island resort. To decide who gets the ticket, Tom and his friends hold a competition to see who can last the longest without using any electronic devices. Tom wins, but when Angela finds that Tom was using an earphone all along, Ben is declared the winner. After Ben leaves, Hank finds out that technology is not allowed on the island.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = When Angela shares her new song, Tom pretends to have liked it so much that he keeps it as a ringtone for his phone. Angela accepts a visit from a music critic who is known to be harsh. The critic seems to be nice and surprised at Angela's kindness, but later publicises a scathing review and gives it a "thumbs-down". Angela ponders giving up her music career, but Tom and friends persuade her to write a song about it, which itself becomes a viral hit.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben has invented a virtual reality device that allows the wearer to imagine their perfect day. Tom tries out Ben's invention and soon finds himself as a successful inventor of a hat locating app. He attracts the attention of the CEO and some aliens. When he refuses to sell his app to the alien, Tom must defend against the invading aliens. He succeeds, but the device overheats and is damaged. When the rest of the gang wants to see what the device recorded as Tom's perfect day, Tom frantically gets rid of the memory storage device.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom and his friends are writing song lyrics. Tom writes about Angela, but is too shy to share with her. When Ginger entertains Tom with a magic trick, Tom finds that Ginger swapped Tom's lyrics with a receipt as part of the trick. Tom tries to get the lyrics back, but Ginger refuses. Tom discovers that Hank was once a famous magician, and tries to learn from him. Tom uses Ben's technology to trap Ginger, and gets the lyrics back. He shows the song to Angela, who thinks the lyrics are about Ben.
|LineColor       =#FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Angered about Hank and Ginger pretending to be pirates and repeatedly restarting a download, Tom and Ben scare Hank and Ginger by telling a made-up story about Big Beard. Because they believe the ghost pirate is real, Hank and Ginger decide to go on a hunt.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom helps Ginger prepare for an eight-and-under tennis tournament. Angela coaches Ginger to win, while Tom coaches Ginger to have fun and enjoy himself. Ginger loses to his opponent, and Tom and Angela try to console him.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Angela becomes infatuated with a movie star named Tanner Von Quads, so Tom orders a "perfect guy starter kit" from a website. When Angela ignores Tom and gets excited about Tanner's appearance at the premiere of his newest film, Tom arrives at the premiere on a motorcycle. He confronts Tanner, then attempts to show off by doing stunts with the motorcycle, only to crash into a fire hydrant. He gets water on Tanner, revealing him to be a robot. The shocked crowd of women chase and beat up Tom. Later, Angela says that she considers Tom to just be a perfect friend, to his dismay.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Willie, Tom's nerdy childhood friend, visits Tom.  Willie is now a cool skateboarder going by the name Will Zee. Tom's friends like Will, and Tom is no longer the centre of attention. To prove that he is also willing to do dangerous and cool things, Tom catapults himself and ends up in the hospital, where he reconciles with Will.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Hank tries adding narration to the episode as he, Tom, Ben, and Ginger wait for a sitcom-like crisis to happen. Angela requests the others to housesit her apartment as a package is scheduled to be delivered, but to not touch anything. While watching TV, the guys learn about "The Banana Berry Bandit", who has been stealing fruit at the local stores, and then find fruit and other suspicious items, leading them to believe that Angela is the criminal. When the postman arrives with the package, the gang ties him up as he says that he is a "federal agent". Angela, angry upon on returning, explains why she had so much fruit: she was making her own line of custom smoothie blenders. The real Banana Berry Bandit is revealed on TV to be a woman who became insane due to malnutrition from her excessive veganism.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ginger disturbs Tom and Ben over their jet pack invention, while Angela works on a jet pack-related song. After watching a "Kid Ninja" episode, and learning that Hank had trained as a ninja, Ginger learns from Hank to be a ninja. When Tom and Ben pick Angela to test the jet pack, Ginger ignores his self-control and steals the jet pack.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = The gang prepares to go to the diner for "Free Milkshake Day". However, when the landlord shows up in the garage with a social media app, Tom becomes obsessed with it, and stays at the garage to take fake pictures of his adventures. Angela returns to the garage to get Tom, only for Tom's mind to be sucked into the app when he gets his millionth friend (per the app's Terms and Conditions). In order to save Tom, Angela must get sucked into the app. By the time Tom returns, the diner is closed and Free Milkshake Day is over.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Angela gives Tom a friendship bracelet and warns him not to break it as that would imply that they are no longer friends. However, in a game of hide-and-seek, Tom gets his hand stuck. He asks for help, but Hank and Ben are soon stuck in other rooms, and Ginger ignores Tom as he wants to win the game. Tom has hallucinations of Angela telling him to cut the bracelet. He does, and frees Ben and Hank.
|LineColor     = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben restores an old handheld computer that turns out to have a program simulating a child. Ben and Tom invite Angela to babysit, but the computer soon "upgrades" into a rebellious teenager and pushes past its hardware limitations, forcing Ben to upload him to the internet.
|LineColor       =#FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom tries to support Angela for a commercial audition, but when Tom starts acting enthusiastically, he gets the part. When he later practices acting and his friends ask him to do impressions, his face freezes up awkwardly, and he is forced to wear a mask made by Ben to make expressions. At the shooting, the mask is overloaded and destroyed, revealing Tom's face. The director likes Tom's expression, and his true face is used in the advertisement.
|LineColor       =#FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = During a heat wave, the landlord does not let Tom and his friends lower the thermostat, password-protecting it using the cloud. With Angela planning to go home and Hank hallucinating, Ben uses a virtual reality device to enter the cloud and hack the thermostat, and Hank tells him the password while hallucinating. When the place gets too cold, Ben's stubbornness results in his friends getting frozen, and Ben realises his mistake when Ginger compares him to the Landlord.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = In a sequel to "The Germinator", Ben gets infected by Jeremy the Germ, who returns from the toilet. Later, Ben transforms into a mindless zombie, spreading the infection across town. Since the gang cannot get infected, they create a plan to cure everyone.
|LineColor       =#FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom and his friends support a basketball team called the Barracudas. Ben shares his newest invention, a tortilla trimming machine, and it inadvertently goes out of control when Angela comes by wearing a t-shirt supporting the Piranhas, a rival team. Music critic Victoria Payne notices Angela's shirt and, being a big Piranhas fan, gets her a gig to sing at the halftime show for the final between the Barracudas and Piranhas. Angela, having to choose between her friends and her career advancement, decides to compromise by singing about a tie game. She is heckled by the audience, and realises that fans from both teams were united on one thing because for her, only for them to be chased by Ben's tortilla trimming machine.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ginger wants Hank to help him build a model rocket for a contest. During a break at the diner, Hank tries a dessert challenge where if he finishes it, then the dish is free, but if he does not, he must pay $500. But when he loses, and he cannot afford to pay, he ends up being the diner's dishwasher. He soon has no time to help Ginger with the rocket, and becomes more tired and irritable. Tom and the gang try to help Hank, and Hank quits the job to help Ginger.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben goes on a trip, warning his friends against touching any of his things while he is away. Tom ignores his warning and touches one of his inventions, creating a wormhole that exchanges Tom with a doppelgänger wearing a bowtie and glasses. He discovers that he has been transported to a parallel universe. Tom enjoys the alternate universe. Meanwhile, in the original universe, Ben and the nerdy Tom develop a dislike for each other due to their similarities, and create a plan to bring the original Tom back with Angela, Ginger and Hank's help. They execute the plan, and Angela sees Tom with the other Angela, making her angry. They bring Tom back to the original universe, revealing that the plan was begun without the nerdy Tom. Ben throws the nerdy Tom into the wormhole and closes it. Angela accuses Tom of being attached to the other Angela; when Tom asks her if she likes him, she tries to deflect.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = After Ginger accidentally breaks Ben's phone during a "Basements and Banshees" trading card game, Ben visits the tech store and falls in love with an employee named Xenon. Tom and Angela give conflicting advice on how to ask her out, but Ben fumbles asking her out. Ben attends a Basements and Banshees tournament where he meets Xenon again, and they play and eliminate every other player.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben is invited to be a featured stand-up comedian at the CEO's birthday party. Tom tells Ben to work on his comedic delivery, so Ben builds a robot named Galileo to help. Galileo initially seems less funny than Ben, but he becomes funny when some vinegar gets into his mouth. When the gang feed Galileo more vinegar, Galileo becomes rude and insulting. At the party, Galileo insults the CEO before Ben destroys him. The CEO is not offended, as he is tired of no one criticising him. Ben makes a joke about the CEO's pet goldfish, which makes the CEO break down and Tom and Ben frantically escape.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben's newest teleportation device accidentally makes Tom and Angela temporarily switch voices when they use it simultaneously. Tom, pretending to be Angela, learns from Angela's mom about a guy named Lance. Believing that Angela is in love with Lance, Tom finds that Lance is a talent promoter and inadvertently makes Lance give Angela an audition for that night. Meanwhile, Ginger steals the device to get an adult voice so that he can order a rocket bike. Tom and Angela go to the audition and perform together so that no one notices which voice is whose. They are selected, but the audience is disturbed when Angela speaks in Tom's voice. When they get home, they find that Hank and Ben had their voices swapped with Ginger.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom and friends play a poker-like game called noodlespoons, when the Landlord arrives to evict them for being too loud. Tom teaches the Landlord the noodlespoons game, but when the Landlord suggests making real bets, Tom wagers his business and loses. The Landlord becomes their boss and turns the company into a cleaning company. Later, Ginger challenges the Landlord to a game of noodlespoons to win back the company.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom forces Ben to take a day off and they, Angela, and Hank go to the Fun Museum, which is boring for everyone except Ben. Meanwhile, Ginger sneaks into the garage and uses Ben's new hover-board, attracting the Landlord's attention. Ginger hides from the Landlord. Tom and his friends, on returning from the museum, find the Landlord sneaking around in the garage, leaving him embarrassed.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben shows off his "Time Rewinder" invention which allows Tom and friends to revisit their past. After being warned by some Bens from the future, Tom convinces Ben to travel back in time with him to prevent Tom creating the invention. On the way, Ben writes on the bathroom mirror at the point in time when Hank and Ginger were fighting a ghost in the 28th episode.
|LineColor       = #FF5F5F
}}
|ShortSummary    =  Part One: During Angela's birthday, she and Ben are the only ones in the diner; Angela accidentally says that she is romantically interested in Tom. Meanwhile, Tom, Hank and Ginger are lost in an empty desert.  Part Two: Worried about Ben keeping her secret, Angela tells Ben an idea for a new invention related to memory. Meanwhile, Tom visits the CEO with Hank playing as Ben, since Ben is not answering. They learn that they are invited to the tech stars conference.  Part Three: Ben invents a mind-erasing device to forget about Angela's secret. Hank was sent to investigate Ben and Angela, but gets distracted and watches television with them. Tom and Ginger attempt to spy at the apartment, but Tom becomes heartbroken due to a misunderstanding, and attempts to sell his and Ben's company.
|LineColor       = FF5F5F
}}
}}
Season 2 (2017–18)
in Season|title=20|director=15|writer=15|airdate=10|episodes=
|ShortSummary    = Three months after the events of the previous episode, everybody except Ginger has memory issues. They keep celebrating Angela's birthday, forget to pay rent, and forget a meeting with the CEO, who had erased their memories.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = After the gang regained their memories, Tom and Angela are surprised that they kissed. They decide to go on a date. At the diner, Angela impatiently waits for Tom while he works on a romantic invention with Ben.
* ''Angela's Songs: "First Date"
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = To avoid romance, the gang (except Ben) goes to the carnival for friendship activities. Ginger tells Tom and Angela to sit together on the ferris wheel, embarrassing them.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    =  Part 1: Hank films Tom and Angela, and Ben and Xenon. Part 2: Tom and Angela compete against Ben and Xenon in Couple Clash''. Before the show, Ben and Xenon cheat by changing the answers, causing Tom and Angela to break up.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben chooses Darren from Tennis Kid to be his new assistant. Ginger becomes angry, because Darren was his rival. Later, they learn Darren is the nephew of the CEO.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = A week after rejecting Ginger, Ben invents a hoverboard with Will Zee's signature as an apology.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = The CEO runs for mayor. Tom mistakenly selling Angela's new song to him. The gang needs to sabotage the campaign and take back Angela's song.
* ''Angela's Songs:'' "We Can Yes"
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben helps Tom run for mayor. When Tom tries Ben's strategy, it seems to work, until the CEO steals the strategy and gains an advantage. Tom and the CEO appear at the "Mayor Factor" challenge to win the audience's votes. During the competition, Ginger helps Tom cheat until Angela catches Ginger and gets mad at Tom. Tom admits to everyone that he cheated, and that he would rather be honest and have his friends than run for mayor. His apology wins the crowd over for his integrity, and he is elected mayor. The CEO also admits that he had cheated and made up lies about Tom and paid for robots to vote for him, but is subsequently ridiculed for it and loses all his votes.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = Newly elected mayor Tom chooses to ensure everyone is happy as his first job as mayor, while Ben suggests fixing the civic infrastructure. Tom creates a booth to field complaints, but that only serves to annoy passers-by. He organises a town party, but when this leaves a huge mess, he cancels the party and creates a clean-up party.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = While practicing a dance routine for the Founder's Day parade, Tom injures his knee. Ben invents the "Brainerator", a device that converts simple talk to intellectual talk so that he can understand what Tom means to say. Under the advice of Xenon, Ben joins a secret intellectual society called the SMARTIES, easily passing their initiation. When he brings the SMARTIES to the garage, they make fun of Ben's friends' intellect, upsetting Ben. Ben sabotages their "No-Brainerator", which the SMARTIES had made so that they could make fun of his friends. Ben quits the SMARTIES and reconciles with Tom at the Founder's Day parade.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = Ben wants Tom to make a promotional video for his Bathroom Buddy app, but Tom and the others become interested in Hank's new food item, the Taco Spaghetti Burger (TSB). A passerby finds it delicious, and the gang converts the garage into a restaurant. Ben gets upset and parts ways with Tom, recruiting Rhonda to promote the app. When the TSB wanes in novelty, Tom and the gang start suggesting other ingredients for Hank, and they continue to have success. Ginger misinterprets a joke Tom said about people drinking toilet water if they thought it was cool, and patrons get sick and start vomiting. Tom rushes to the diner to apologise to Ben.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary    = Tom and Angela have a double-date scavenger hunt adventure with Ben and Xenon (via webcam). At the diner, a storm blows a tree in front of the door, trapping them inside. They try to keep themselves entertained, but Ginger warns them that a monster is nearby. The gang tries to contact Hank to bring a robot to cut down the tree, but they lose reception. When the diner is hit by a power outage, the rest of the customers follow Ginger and tie up Tom and Angela for not following Ginger. A robot controlled by Xenon arrives, with Xenon explaining all the strange events.
|LineColor       = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = Tom and Ben finish their business plan, but Tom mistakenly sends the document to the CEO. Ben creates a device that teleports him and Tom into the Internet to chase down the email, with Ginger helping them navigate. Meanwhile, Hank and Angela try to distract the CEO from opening his email. In the end, Tom and Ben succeed by infecting the CEO's phone with computer viruses.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = The gang wants to go to a demolition derby but is unable to because Ginger's babysitter has hidden the tickets. Tom offers to become the babysitter, but realises Ginger's carefree activity puts him in danger, so he puts Ginger in a person-sized hamster ball. The gang gets upset that Tom is becoming overprotective, and they trap Tom in the ball.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = The gang celebrates their annual garage feast day, which consists of gathering food which has gone past or is near the expiration date. Ben invites his computer son Boomerang, who brings his girlfriend, a dot matrix printer named Dot. Boomerang talks about how and he and Dot have developed artwork on display at a local museum, but Ben is concerned he is wasting his time, and almost ruins his relationship with Boomerang.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = Ben is looking for his new invention, the Miracle Slurper, when Ginger informs them that the invention that it Tom has been confiscated by his teacher after it was lent to Ginger by Tom. Tom and Angela dress up as Ginger's parents, but at the school, Tom learns that Ginger's teacher was also Tom's former teacher, Ms. Vanthrax. Ms. Vanthrax sees through Tom's and Angela's disguises and gives them all detention, leaving Ben with only one option: to sneak into the school and get Tom, Angela and Ginger. Ben succeeds, but chooses to let Ms. Vanthrax keep Tom in detention for giving the invention to Ginger.
