}}
|ShortSummary = Xenon tells Ben that she will be in town, but when Ben learns Xenon went on a drive with her coworker Albert, Ben insists on driving her around as well. After restoring an old taxicab that was lying in front of the garage, Ben reveals to Tom that he does not know how to drive, but realises he can make a remote control to drive the car. The driving date goes well until Ginger, Hank and Angela unknowingly use the remote to try to operate Ginger's RC car.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = When Hank learns that his favorite show, Bongo & McGillicuddy, is ending, he uses Ben's invention to enter the TV world to convince the two not to retire. While there, he learns that Bongo and McGillicuddy see the world Hank lives in as a television show as well. With Ben's invention broken, Hank, Bongo and McGillicuddy must recover their version of the inter-dimensional transporter from Bongo and McGilicuddy's nemesis Dr. Technology, who has escaped from jail.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = Tom and the gang are excited to see the eighth installment of the Space Conflicts film series, but are shocked when Angela reveals she has never watched it. Tom lends her a copy of the entire series, but she falls asleep trying to watch them. In a panic, she chooses learn all the basics about the series from Xenon so that she can pretend to be a fan and avoid offending Tom again. She almost convinces everyone, only to end up sleeping through the movie's premiere as she did when she tried watching the previous movies.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = Ben invents a Santa Claus tracker, finding that Santa has disappeared at the CEO's building. Tom and the gang try to sneak Ginger into the CEO's office, but they are captured. The gang convince Darren to help them, and they are able to track Santa to a room. However, Santa will not let himself be rescued until they can restore the CEO's "Christmas spirit", and teaches the CEO a Christmas lesson.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = Angela suffers from stage fright in front of celebrity judge Ricky Deluna, so Tom and the gang give her a wig, saying that people act more confident when in disguise. With the wig, she becomes Angie Fierce, her more confident alter ego. After succeeding in auditions, Angela continues to wear the wig but her new Angie Fierce personality makes her more rude, with removing the wig being the only way to make Angela her normal self. Angela's original personality eventually succeeds in getting rid of the wig, and Angela returns to her normal self.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = The Landlord chooses to sell the garage so he can move to the islands and find his soulmate. Tom and the gang scramble to find a reason for him to stay. They stop the CEO, who offered to buy the garage, from demolishing the garage. They succeed by convincing Ginger's teacher, Ms. Vanthrax, and the Landlord to meet Tom. They eventually succeed, though Ginger gets in trouble for mocking Ms. Vanthrax.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = The CEO promotes Darren to intern, and tasks him with cleaning the goldfish bowl. Darren accidentally trips while cleaning the fish bowl, and the fish falls out a window, landing in Hank's slush drink. Hank takes care of the fish until Tom and the gang learn it is the CEO's fish and they convince Hank to return him. The CEO does not believe them until Darren slips and nearly lets the fish out of the window again. The CEO lets Tom and Hank leave without getting caught by security.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = Ginger has a bag full of coins, but the Landlord takes the money to make up for his rent hike, saying that his psychic has quit and he needs a new one. Hank discovers that Ginger has been stealing the coins from the town's wishing fountain, and warns Ginger of bad luck, which comes true. Meanwhile, Tom convinces Angela to become the Landlord's psychic, but soon she tires the job and she tries to convince the Landlord that he has psychic powers. The Landlord learns that Angela was fooling him, but makes two predictions in a fit of anger, both of which come true convincing himself that he is a psychic. Ginger gets the coins back and runs to return them, only to find that the fountain has been dug out for renovations.
|LineColor = #00FF00
}}
|ShortSummary = In Angela's apartment, the gang is playing a mystery detective role-playing game where the players must find out which one among them is a jewel thief. Tom finds Angela's diary and reads it, learning that Angela is keeping a secret. Tom becomes curious but decides not to betray Angela's trust, then his character card talks to him as a hallucination and goads him into finding out the truth. Ben and Angela accuse Tom of being the jewel thief, and Tom accuses Angela of hiding a secret and storms out of the apartment. Angela says that she was going to do a music video with Ricky DeLuna and wanted to reveal it only when it was confirmed. Tom reveals his snooping, and Angela is disgusted. In anger, Tom throws his hat and character card away, and tries to apologise to Angela, but to no avail.
