|ShortSummary = When Ginger and Angela's kiteboarding race in the park gets cancelled due to a thunderstorm, despite Action Weatherman Skip Flipper saying that it was going to be sunny, Ben, who is now able to use tech, invents a weather machine that can make the weather calm for Skip. However, after the weather becomes absurd with raining diapers and screaming clouds, Tom goes to the TV station to investigate, but is stopped by Skip. Tom pushes him aside and discovers that Skip had damaged the machine because no one was watching his reports when the weather was calm. Skip sarcastically confesses, and Tom reveals that Hank, Angela and Ginger had recorded and broadcast Skip's confession. Ben sees the confession on TV, and leaves to help Tom after Skip damages the machine further, causing a tornado made of garbage, and successfully shuts down the machine while his friends shield him from debris. Later, Ben tells his friends that he has made some changes to the machine so that the machine gives calm weather only sometimes, and see Skip on TV, hosting his show from prison, and saying that the weather will be "sunny and drier than prison pot roast", only for it to start raining at that moment.
|LineColor = #FF2CFF
}}
|ShortSummary = Tom and the gang get ready for their annual dance party, which has been changed from a tropical-themed party to a snow-themed "Snow Ball" after the water pipes burst, with Becca creating the playlist. Later, while shopping with Ben, Angela sees Becca ostensibly flirting with Tom, and confronts Tom about it. Tom denies having flirted, and Angela leaves in disgust, and has a "pity party" for herself at the diner, when Rhonda tells her to go with another date to make Tom feel desperate. At the party, Angela arrives with the MC, while Ben tells Tom that Becca seems to really like Tom. On seeing Angela with MC, Tom goes with Becca for a dance, when Angela announces that there is a boyfriend stealer in the party. Becca confesses that she had a crush on Hank and that Tom kept on getting in her way when she wanted to subtly show her love, when a speaker explodes and everyone runs out in fright. Angela records herself talking about how the party was terrible and that Tom will never speak to her again, when Tom arrives and tells her that if Angela had not forgiven him every time Tom made a mistake, they would have broken up long ago, and comforts Angela, and the friends return and have their party.
|LineColor = #FF2CFF
}}
|ShortSummary = The CEO leaves town, putting his pet goldfish Goldie in charge. Hank is put in charge of the headquarters as Goldie is deemed incapable of making decisions. However, he finds it boring and adds fun activities to the tower. A hallucination of the CEO tells Hank to give him "a power smile", which ends up making him evil-minded and putting his friends in danger.
|LineColor = #FF2CFF
}}
|ShortSummary = While at the Chocolate Museum, the friends learn about the "Chocolate Games", a tournament in which the last player standing gets a giant chocolate statue. Darren enters the game, and Ben and Hank are the first to be eliminated. Later, Ginger is eliminated by Darren, but notices that Darren's chocolate did not fall off his helmet. In the end, Tom and Angela are eliminated, and Darren is declared the winner. However, Ginger goes back to the forest where the game was held and collects evidence and convinces the gang that Darren is cheating. They investigate and find that the museum owner let Darren cheat in exchange for Nougat Lisa, and gatecrash the awards ceremony and prove that Darren and the owner had cheated. An angry crowd chases them away, and the statue is divided amongst the public, though the chocolate pieces are the same size as the small pieces given to the  visitors. Later, Ginger leaves with a full arm of the statue.
|LineColor = #FF2CFF
}}
|ShortSummary = After Ginger's basketball team loses yet another game, Ginger asks Hank to return to third grade in order to be eligible to participate in Ginger's team. However, Hank fails his test and is told by Ms. Vanthrax that if he fails the next one, he will not be allowed to participate in the sport team. Hank is pressured by Ronnie and Darren to sneak into Ms. Vanthrax's room and get the test answers. Ginger tells Tom, Ben and Angela that Hank is falling with a bad group, and they find Hank missing from his room. Meanwhile, Hank returns to school under the pretext of returning the team mascot costume when his friends find him and try to stop him; Ginger agrees to steal the test answers so that things will be easier. Hank decides to not cheat so that Ginger will not, and passes the test by studying all night. During the basketball game, Ginger scores at the last moment, only to be disappointed that Hank is asleep and has not seen him score.
|LineColor = #FF2CFF
}}
|ShortSummary = The friends are invited to a party in the storage room, but seeing all of them run into the room, they realise that is actually a trap set up by an unknown person. Bongo and McGillicuddy (who are watching the episode) investigate by using various episode clips from throughout the show to reveal the villain and discover that the culprit is the very first villain in the series: Gilbert from "Friendly Customer Service". Meanwhile, Hank realises that Gilbert is the villain, and Ginger reveals that he had turned Gilbert back on, so the friends pretend to like the room. Gilbert shows himself and enters the room, and the friends unplug him.
|LineColor = #FF2CFF
}}
|ShortSummary = Angela tells Tom that she took a quiz that says that their relationship is boring, and Tom says that he has to go to renew his business licence. Later, Xenon arrives and tells Angela that the Agency has created a satellite that can destroy gravity with the intention of sending everyone floating into space, and that Angela and Xenon must travel to an alternate dimension where Tom works for the Agency, so that they can get the password to  disable the satellite. Xenon gags the other Angela and Xenon to impersonate them, and goes out with the original Angela, Tom and Ben. Angela, to her horror, finds that she is falling for the Tom working for the Agency even though he is evil. Later, Angela manages to find the password from Tom when the other Angela and Xenon arrive, and the original Angela and Xenon escape and get rid of the evil Tom. Xenon successfully destroys the satellite and leaves.
|LineColor = #FF2CFF
}}
